README.rst
     1→.. image:: https://github.com/agronholm/typeguard/actions/workflows/test.yml/badge.svg
     2→  :target: https://github.com/agronholm/typeguard/actions/workflows/test.yml
     3→  :alt: Build Status
     4→.. image:: https://coveralls.io/repos/agronholm/typeguard/badge.svg?branch=master&service=github
     5→  :target: https://coveralls.io/github/agronholm/typeguard?branch=master
     6→  :alt: Code Coverage
     7→.. image:: https://readthedocs.org/projects/typeguard/badge/?version=latest
     8→  :target: https://typeguard.readthedocs.io/en/latest/?badge=latest
     9→  :alt: Documentation
    10→.. image:: https://tidelift.com/badges/package/pypi/typeguard
    11→  :target: https://tidelift.com/subscription/pkg/pypi-typeguard
    12→  :alt: Tidelift
    13→
    14→This library provides run-time type checking for functions defined with
    15→`PEP 484 <https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0484/>`_ argument (and return) type
    16→annotations, and any arbitrary objects. It can be used together with static type
    17→checkers as an additional layer of type safety, to catch type violations that could only
    18→be detected at run time.
    19→
    20→Two principal ways to do type checking are provided:
    21→
    22→#. The ``check_type`` function:
    23→
    24→   * like ``isinstance()``, but supports arbitrary type annotations (within limits)
    25→   * can be used as a ``cast()`` replacement, but with actual checking of the value
    26→#. Code instrumentation:
    27→
    28→   * entire modules, or individual functions (via ``@typechecked``) are recompiled, with
    29→     type checking code injected into them
    30→   * automatically checks function arguments, return values and assignments to annotated
    31→     local variables
    32→   * for generator functions (regular and async), checks yield and send values
    33→   * requires the original source code of the instrumented module(s) to be accessible
    34→
    35→Two options are provided for code instrumentation:
    36→
    37→#. the ``@typechecked`` function:
    38→
    39→   * can be applied to functions individually
    40→#. the import hook (``typeguard.install_import_hook()``):
    41→
    42→   * automatically instruments targeted modules on import
    43→   * no manual code changes required in the target modules
    44→   * requires the import hook to be installed before the targeted modules are imported
    45→   * may clash with other import hooks
    46→
    47→See the documentation_ for further information.
    48→
      →…

